# Styling — NativeWind + Mingo Design Tokens

ALL styling uses NativeWind `className`. See `mingo-ui-guide.md` and `tailwind.config.js`.

## Always Use Design Tokens

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — hardcoded hex / arbitrary values
<View style={{ backgroundColor: '#768D85' }} />
<View className="bg-[#F1F4F3]" />

// ✅ GOOD — semantic tokens from tailwind.config.js
<View className="bg-primary" />
<View className="bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark" />
```

## Mingo Color Tokens (configured in tailwind.config.js)

| Use case | Token |
|---|---|
| Brand / active / CTA | `bg-primary` (#768D85) |
| Screen background | `bg-background-light dark:bg-background-dark` |
| Card / input bg | `bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark` |
| Body text | `text-text-light dark:text-text-dark` |
| Secondary text | `text-text-secondary-light dark:text-text-secondary-dark` |
| Placeholder / disabled | `text-text-muted-light dark:text-text-muted-dark` |
| Borders | `border-border-light dark:border-border-dark` |
| Destructive | `bg-danger-light dark:bg-danger-dark` |
| Online dot | `bg-online-light` |

## Dark Mode

ALWAYS pair light + dark variants for surface/text/border:

```tsx
<View className="bg-background-light dark:bg-background-dark">
  <Text className="text-text-light dark:text-text-dark">Hello</Text>
</View>
```

## Typography

Use the `<Text>` component from `@/components/ui` (NOT raw `<Text>` from `react-native`):

```tsx
import { Text } from '@/components/ui';

<Text variant="title">Heading</Text>     // h1 28/700
<Text variant="subtitle">Subhead</Text>  // 22/700
<Text>Body</Text>                        // default 16/400
<Text variant="muted">Caption</Text>
```

Font family classes: `font-regular`, `font-medium`, `font-semibold`, `font-bold` (Montserrat).

## Spacing & Radius

- Horizontal screen padding: `px-4` (16px) — consistent across app
- Pills / buttons / inputs: `rounded-full`
- Cards: `rounded-lg` (16px)
- Avatars: `rounded-full`, sizes 32 / 40 / 48 / 80

## Composing Classes

Use `tailwind-merge` (`twMerge`) to safely merge override className from props:

```tsx
import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge';

<View className={twMerge('px-4 py-2 bg-primary', className)} />
```

## Don'ts

- ❌ NO `StyleSheet.create` for new code — NativeWind only
- ❌ NO inline `style={{ color: '#...' }}` for theme-able colors
- ❌ NO `#F5F5F5`, `#2C2C2E`, `#4A7C6A` (legacy values — see UI guide §7)
- ❌ NO divider lines — use spacing instead (per UI guide)
